## 7. ☁️ High Availability Cluster Design

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Active-Active Cluster"
        NODE1["🖥️ Node 1\n(Active — Primary)"]
        NODE2["🖥️ Node 2\n(Active — Secondary)"]
        NODE3["🖥️ Node 3\n(Standby)"]
    end

    subgraph "Load Balancer"
        LB["⚖️ ECMP / BGP Load Balancer\n(Health-check based)"]
    end

    subgraph "State Synchronization"
        ETCD["📦 etcd Cluster\n(Leader Election / Raft)"]
        SYNC["🔄 State Sync\n(ConnTrack replication)"]
    end

    subgraph "Shared State"
        SESS["📡 Session Table\n(replicated)"]
        POLICY["📋 Policy Store\n(versioned)"]
        MODELS["🧠 Model Registry\n(shared FS / S3)"]
    end

    CLIENT["🌐 Client Traffic"] --> LB
    LB --> NODE1 & NODE2
    NODE3 -.->|"hot standby"| NODE1

    NODE1 & NODE2 & NODE3 <--> ETCD
    NODE1 <-->|"state replication"| SYNC
    NODE2 <-->|"state replication"| SYNC

    SYNC <--> SESS & POLICY & MODELS
```

**Failure Scenarios:**

| السيناريو | الاكتشاف | الاستجابة | RTO |
|---|---|---|---|
| Node 1 crash | Health-check (1s) | LB removes node 1 | < 3s |
| Network partition | etcd quorum loss | Leader election | < 5s |
| Split-brain | Raft consensus | Highest-ID wins | < 10s |
| Model corruption | Checksum validation | Rollback to prev | < 30s |

