## 10. 📡 Network Architecture Details

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph "Physical Interfaces"
        WAN["🌐 WAN Interface\n(eth0 — Public IP)"]
        LAN["🏠 LAN Interface\n(eth1 — 192.168.0.0/24)"]
        DMZ["🔒 DMZ Interface\n(eth2 — 10.0.1.0/24)"]
        MGMT["⚙️ MGMT Interface\n(eth3 — 172.16.0.0/24)"]
    end

    subgraph "Transparent Proxy Mode"
        TP["🔄 iptables REDIRECT\nTCP 80,443 → 8080,8443"]
        TPROXY["🔐 TPROXY\n(preserve original dst)"]
    end

    subgraph "TLS Interception Pipeline"
        CLI_HELLO["Client Hello (TLS 1.3)"]
        JA3["JA3/JA4 Fingerprint\n(before decryption)"]
        BUMP["🔐 SSL Bump\n(re-sign with CA)"]
        INSPECT["DPI on plaintext\n(WAF / DLP / Malware)"]
        FORWARD["Re-encrypt to server"]
    end

    subgraph "NAT Architecture"
        MASQ["MASQUERADE\n(hide client IPs)"]
        SNAT["SNAT (static)\n(server published services)"]
        DNAT["DNAT (port forward)\n(DMZ exposure)"]
    end

    WAN --> TP & TPROXY
    TP --> CLI_HELLO --> JA3 --> BUMP --> INSPECT --> FORWARD
    LAN --> MASQ --> WAN
    MASQ --> SNAT & DNAT
```

**TLS Inspection Limits:**
| Scenario | الإجراء |
|---|---|
| Certificate Pinning (HPKP) | Bypass (no inspection) — avoid MiTM |
| Banking / Health domains | Exemption list (no inspection) |
| Expired/Self-signed cert | Block + user warning |
| ESNI / ECH traffic | Metadata analysis only |

